#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:0.4"
msgid "Bhojanavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 32"

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:0.5"
msgid "32. Gaṇabhojanasikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on group meals"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:1.0b"
msgid ""
msgstr "First sub-story"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-cs-bu-pc32.1, pts-vp-en.2.306, ms2V_678
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Rājagaha in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrel sanctuary."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena devadatto parihīnalābhasakkāro sapariso kulesu viññāpetvā viññāpetvā bhuñjati."
msgstr "At that time, because of decline in support and loss of respect, Devadatta and his followers were only invited to meals after repeatedly asking."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:1.3"
msgid "Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "People grumbled and complained,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:1.4"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā kulesu viññāpetvā viññāpetvā bhuñjissanti."
msgstr "“How can the Sakyan ascetics eat at invitations after repeatedly asking?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:1.5"
msgid "Kassa sampannaṃ na manāpaṃ, kassa sāduṃ na ruccatī”ti."
msgstr "Who doesn’t like nice food? Who doesn’t want tasty food?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, ms2V_679
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:1.6"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ."
msgstr "The monks heard those people grumbling and complaining,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:1.7"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:1.8"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized those monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:1.9"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma devadatto sapariso kulesu viññāpetvā viññāpetvā bhuñjissatī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "“How can Devadatta and his followers eat at invitations after repeatedly asking?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:1.10"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, devadatta, sapariso kulesu viññāpetvā viññāpetvā bhuñjasī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, Devadatta, that you do this?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:1.11"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:1.12"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:1.13"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, sapariso kulesu viññāpetvā viññāpetvā bhuñjissasi."
msgstr "Foolish man, how can you and your followers eat at invitations after repeatedly asking?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:1.14"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:1.15"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:1.15a"
msgid ""
msgstr "First preliminary ruling"

#. HTML: </h3><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc3, pts-vp-en.2.307, ms2V_680
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:1.16"
msgid "“Gaṇabhojane pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk eats in a group, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p class="endsection">
#. REF: sc4, ms2V_681
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:1.17"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second sub-story"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: sc5, pts-vp-pli4.72, pts-cs-bu-pc32.2, ms2V_682
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena manussā gilāne bhikkhū bhattena nimantenti."
msgstr "Soon afterwards people invited sick monks to a meal."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:2.2"
msgid "Bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā nādhivāsenti—“paṭikkhittaṃ bhagavatā gaṇabhojanan”ti."
msgstr "Knowing that the Master had prohibited eating meals in a group and being afraid of wrongdoing, they did not accept."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:2.3"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "They told the Master."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:2.4"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards he gave a teaching and addressed the monks,"

#. HTML: <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:2.5"
msgid "“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, gilānena bhikkhunā gaṇabhojanaṃ bhuñjituṃ."
msgstr "“Monks, I allow a sick monk to eat in a group."

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:2.6"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:2.6a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second preliminary ruling"

#. HTML: </h3><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc6, ms2V_683
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:2.7"
msgid "“Gaṇabhojane, aññatra samayā, pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "‘If a monk eats in a group, unless there is an appropriate reason, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:2.8"
msgid "Tatthāyaṃ samayo."
msgstr "The appropriate reason is this:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:2.9"
msgid "Gilānasamayo—ayaṃ tattha samayo”ti."
msgstr "he is sick.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p class="endsection">
#. REF: sc7, ms2V_684
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:2.10"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Third sub-story"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: sc8, pts-cs-bu-pc32.3, ms2V_685
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:3.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena manussā cīvaradānasamaye sacīvarabhattaṃ paṭiyādetvā bhikkhū nimantenti—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards, during the robe-giving season, people prepared a meal together with robe-cloth and then invited the monks, saying,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:3.2"
msgid "“bhojetvā cīvarena acchādessāmā”ti."
msgstr "“We wish to offer you a meal and then give you robe-cloth.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:3.3"
msgid "Bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā nādhivāsenti—“paṭikkhittaṃ bhagavatā gaṇabhojanan”ti."
msgstr "Knowing that the Master had prohibited eating meals in a group and being afraid of wrongdoing, they did not accept."

#. REF: pts-vp-en.2.308
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:3.4"
msgid "Cīvaraṃ parittaṃ uppajjati."
msgstr "As a result they only obtained a small amount of robe-cloth."

#. VAR: Bhagavato → bhikkhū bhagavato (c1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:3.5"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "They told the Master. …"

#. HTML: <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:3.6"
msgid "anujānāmi, bhikkhave, cīvaradānasamaye gaṇabhojanaṃ bhuñjituṃ."
msgstr "“Monks, I allow you to eat in a group during the robe-giving season."

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:3.7"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:3.7a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Third preliminary ruling"

#. HTML: </h3><p><span class="rule">
#. REF: sc9, ms2V_686
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:3.8"
msgid "“Gaṇabhojane, aññatra samayā, pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "‘If a monk eats in a group, unless there is an appropriate reason, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:3.9"
msgid "Tatthāyaṃ samayo."
msgstr "The appropriate reasons are these:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:3.10"
msgid "Gilānasamayo, cīvaradānasamayo—ayaṃ tattha samayo”ti."
msgstr "he is sick, it is the robe-giving season.’”"

