msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:7.7"
msgid "“Gaṇabhojane, aññatra samayā, pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "‘If a monk eats in a group, unless there is an appropriate reason, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:7.8"
msgid "Tatthāyaṃ samayo."
msgstr "The appropriate reasons are these:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:7.9"
msgid "Gilānasamayo, cīvaradānasamayo, cīvarakārasamayo, addhānagamanasamayo, nāvābhiruhanasamayo, mahāsamayo—ayaṃ tattha samayo”ti."
msgstr "he is sick, it is the robe-giving season, he is making a robe, he is traveling on a main road, he is traveling by boat, it is a big occasion.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p class="endsection">
#. REF: sc22, ms2V_699
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:7.10"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:8.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Eighth sub-story"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: sc23, pts-vp-pli4.74, pts-cs-bu-pc32.8, ms2V_700
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:8.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena rañño māgadhassa seniyassa bimbisārassa ñātisālohito ājīvakesu pabbajito hoti."
msgstr "Soon afterwards a relative of King Seniya Bimbisāra of Magadha who had gone forth with the Ājīvaka ascetics"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:8.2"
msgid "Atha kho so ājīvako yena rājā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "approached the King"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:8.3"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā rājānaṃ māgadhaṃ seniyaṃ bimbisāraṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:8.4"
msgid "“icchāmahaṃ, mahārāja, sabbapāsaṇḍikabhattaṃ kātun”ti."
msgstr "“Great King, I wish to make a meal for the ascetics of all sects.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:8.5"
msgid "“Sace tvaṃ, bhante, buddhappamukhaṃ bhikkhusaṃghaṃ paṭhamaṃ bhojeyyāsi”."
msgstr "“That’s fine, Venerable, if you first feed the Order of monks headed by the Buddha.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:8.6"
msgid "“Evaṃ kareyyāmī”ti."
msgstr "“I’ll do that.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:8.7"
msgid "Atha kho so ājīvako bhikkhūnaṃ santike dūtaṃ pāhesi—"
msgstr "And he sent a message to the monks:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:8.8"
msgid "“adhivāsentu me bhikkhū svātanāya bhattan”ti."
msgstr "“Please accept a meal from me tomorrow.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:8.9"
msgid "Bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā nādhivāsenti—“paṭikkhittaṃ bhagavatā gaṇabhojanan”ti."
msgstr "But knowing that the Master had prohibited eating meals in a group and being afraid of wrongdoing, they did not accept."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:8.10"
msgid "Atha kho so ājīvako yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "That Ājīvaka ascetic then went to the Master,"

#. REF: pts-vp-en.2.311
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:8.11"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi, sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi."
msgstr "exchanged friendly greetings with him, and stood to one side."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:8.12"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho so ājīvako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "And he said this,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:8.13"
msgid "“bhavampi gotamo pabbajito, ahampi pabbajito;"
msgstr "“Good Gotama has gone forth and so have I."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:8.14"
msgid "arahati pabbajito pabbajitassa piṇḍaṃ paṭiggahetuṃ."
msgstr "One who has gone forth is entitled to give alms to another who has gone forth."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:8.15"
msgid "Adhivāsetu me bhavaṃ gotamo svātanāya bhattaṃ saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṃghenā”ti."
msgstr "Good Gotama, please accept a meal from me tomorrow together with the Order of monks.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:8.16"
msgid "Adhivāsesi bhagavā tuṇhībhāvena."
msgstr "The Master consented by remaining silent."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:8.17"
msgid "Atha kho so ājīvako bhagavato adhivāsanaṃ viditvā pakkāmi."
msgstr "The Ājīvaka understood that the Master had consented, and he left."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:8.18"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards the Master gave a teaching and addressed the monks,"

#. HTML: <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:8.19"
msgid "“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, samaṇabhattasamaye gaṇabhojanaṃ bhuñjituṃ."
msgstr "“Monks, I allow you to eat in a group when the meal is given by an ascetic."

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:8.20"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:8.20a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc24, ms2V_701
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:8.21"
msgid "Gaṇabhojane, aññatra samayā, pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "‘If a monk eats in a group, unless there is an appropriate reason, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:8.22"
msgid "Tatthāyaṃ samayo."
msgstr "The appropriate reasons are these:"

#. VAR: nāvābhiruhanasamayo → nāvābhirūhana ... (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:8.23"
msgid "Gilānasamayo, cīvaradānasamayo, cīvarakārasamayo, addhānagamanasamayo, nāvābhiruhanasamayo, mahāsamayo, samaṇabhattasamayo—ayaṃ tattha samayo”ti."
msgstr "he is sick, it is the robe-giving season, he is making a robe, he is traveling on a main road, he is traveling by boat, it is a big occasion, it is a meal given by an ascetic.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:9.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc25, pts-cs-bu-pc32.9.1, ms2V_702
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:9.1.1"
msgid "Gaṇabhojanaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Eats in a group:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:9.1.2"
msgid "yattha cattāro bhikkhū pañcannaṃ bhojanānaṃ aññatarena bhojanena nimantitā bhuñjanti."
msgstr "wherever four monks, after being invited, eat any of the five staple foods—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:9.1.3"
msgid "Etaṃ gaṇabhojanaṃ nāma."
msgstr "this is called “eats in a group."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc26, ms2V_703
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:9.1.4"
msgid "Aññatra samayāti"
msgstr "Unless there is an appropriate reason:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:9.1.5"
msgid "ṭhapetvā samayaṃ."
msgstr "except at an appropriate time."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc27, ms2V_704,  
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:9.1.6"
msgid "Gilānasamayo nāma"
msgstr "He is sick:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
#. VAR: phalitā → phālitā (bj, s1-3, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:9.1.7"
msgid "antamaso pādāpi phalitā honti."
msgstr "even if he just has split feet,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:9.1.8"
msgid "“Gilānasamayo”ti bhuñjitabbaṃ."
msgstr "he may eat in a group."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc28, ms2V_705
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:9.1.9"
msgid "Cīvaradānasamayo nāma"
msgstr "It is the robe-giving season:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
# NOTE: That is, the last month of the rainy season, plus the four months of the cold season. 
#. REF: pts-vp-en.2.312
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:9.1.10"
msgid "anatthate kathine vassānassa pacchimo māso, atthate kathine pañcamāsā. “Cīvaradānasamayo”ti bhuñjitabbaṃ."
msgstr "if he has not done the robe-making ceremony, he may eat in a group during the last month of the rainy season. If he has done the robe-making ceremony, he may eat in a group during the five month period."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc29, ms2V_706
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:9.1.11"
msgid "Cīvarakārasamayo nāma"
msgstr "He is making a robe:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
# NOTE: According to the commentary, [](Sp.4.813.4), “Whoever does any work to be done in regard to the robe—the Mahāpaccariya says, ‘Even one who just threads the needle’—may eat a group meal because he is making a robe,” _yo tattha cīvare kattabbaṃ yaṃkiñci kammaṃ karoti, mahāpaccariyañhi “antamaso sūcivedhanako”tipi vuttaṃ, tena cīvarakārasamayoti bhuñjitabbaṃ_. 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:9.1.12"
msgid "cīvare kayiramāne."
msgstr "if he is making a robe,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:9.1.13"
msgid "“Cīvarakārasamayo”ti bhuñjitabbaṃ."
msgstr "he may eat in a group."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc30, pts-vp-pli4.75, ms2V_707
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:9.1.14"
msgid "Addhānagamanasamayo nāma"
msgstr "He is traveling on a main road:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
# NOTE: Half a _yojana_. The length of a _yojana_ is uncertain, and perhaps it never was a precise distance. But a reasonable estimate is 8 miles or just under 13 kilometers (see ACMC, p.16). Thus half a _yojana_ is just over 6 km. 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:9.1.15"
msgid "“addhayojanaṃ gacchissāmī”ti bhuñjitabbaṃ, gacchantena bhuñjitabbaṃ, gatena bhuñjitabbaṃ."
msgstr "if he intends to travel at least six kilometers, he may eat in a group. And he may eat in a group while he is traveling, and after traveling."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc31, ms2V_708
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:9.1.16"
msgid "Nāvābhiruhanasamayo nāma"
msgstr "He is traveling by boat:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:9.1.17"
msgid "“nāvaṃ abhiruhissāmī”ti bhuñjitabbaṃ, āruḷhena bhuñjitabbaṃ, oruḷhena bhuñjitabbaṃ."
msgstr "if he intends to board a boat, he may eat in a group. And he may eat in a group while on-board, and after disembarking."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc32, ms2V_709
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:9.1.18"
msgid "Mahāsamayo nāma"
msgstr "It is a big occasion:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:9.1.19"
msgid "yattha dve tayo bhikkhū piṇḍāya caritvā yāpenti, catutthe āgate na yāpenti."
msgstr "if two or three monks can get by by walking for alms, but not a group of four,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:9.1.20"
msgid "“Mahāsamayo”ti bhuñjitabbaṃ."
msgstr "he may eat in a group."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc33, ms2V_710
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:9.1.21"
msgid "Samaṇabhattasamayo nāma"
msgstr "It is a meal given by an ascetic:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:9.1.22"
msgid "yo koci paribbājakasamāpanno bhattaṃ karoti."
msgstr "if any kind of wanderer is making the meal,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:9.1.23"
msgid "“Samaṇabhattasamayo”ti bhuñjitabbaṃ."
msgstr "he may eat in a group."

#. HTML: </span></p><hr><p>
#. REF: sc34, ms2V_711
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:9.1.24"
msgid "“Aññatra samayā bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he receives it intending to eat it, unless there is an appropriate reason, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:9.1.25"
msgid "Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "For every mouthful, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:9.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc35, pts-cs-bu-pc32.9.2, ms2V_712
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:9.2.1"
msgid "Gaṇabhojane gaṇabhojanasaññī, aññatra samayā, bhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it is a group meal, and he perceives it as a group meal, and he eats, unless there is an appropriate reason, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:9.2.2"
msgid "Gaṇabhojane vematiko, aññatra samayā, bhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it is a group meal, but he is unsure if it is, and he eats, unless there is an appropriate reason, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:9.2.3"
msgid "Gaṇabhojane nagaṇabhojanasaññī, aññatra samayā, bhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it is a group meal, but he does not perceive it as a group meal, and he eats, unless there is an appropriate reason, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc36, ms2V_713
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:9.2.4"
msgid "Nagaṇabhojane gaṇabhojanasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is not a group meal, but he perceives it as a group meal, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. REF: pts-vp-en.2.313
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:9.2.5"
msgid "Nagaṇabhojane vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is not a group meal, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:9.2.6"
msgid "Nagaṇabhojane nagaṇabhojanasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr "If it is not a group meal, and he does not perceive it as a group meal, there is no offense."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:9.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc37, pts-cs-bu-pc32.9.3, ms2V_714
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:9.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:9.3.2"
msgid "samaye,"
msgstr "if there is an appropriate reason;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:9.3.3"
msgid "dve tayo ekato bhuñjanti,"
msgstr "if two or three eat together;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:9.3.4"
msgid "piṇḍāya caritvā ekato sannipatitvā bhuñjanti,"
msgstr "if they eat together after walking for alms;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:9.3.5"
msgid "salākabhattaṃ,"
msgstr "if it is a regular meal invitation;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:9.3.6"
msgid "niccabhattaṃ,"
msgstr "if it is a meal invitation decided by drawing lots;"

# NOTE: One of the sub-commentaries says: _Ekasmiṃ pakkhe ekadivasaṃ dātabbaṃ bhattaṃ pakkhikaṃ_, “_pakkhikaṃ_ means: meal to be given one day in one half-month.” (Sp-ṭ.2.30).
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:9.3.7"
msgid "pakkhikaṃ,"
msgstr "if it is a half-monthly meal;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:9.3.8"
msgid "uposathikaṃ,"
msgstr "if it is on the observance day;"

#. REF: pts-vp-en.2.314
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:9.3.9"
msgid "pāṭipadikaṃ,"
msgstr "if it is on the day after the observance day;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:9.3.10"
msgid "pañca bhojanāni ṭhapetvā sabbattha anāpatti,"
msgstr "if it is anything apart from the five staple foods;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:9.3.11"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:9.3.12"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. HTML: </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc38, ms2V_715
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc32:9.3.13"
msgid "Gaṇabhojanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dutiyaṃ."
msgstr "The second rule, the training rule on group meals, is finished."
